  "text": "The highest derivative of the solid fraction φ implies that we require one boundary condition to determine φ in the mushy layer. Conservation of solute leads us to deduce that φ = 0 at the mush-liquid interface whenever flow is from the liquid into the mush [CITATION_1] .",
